# Branding: macro colors and icons

Use this theme convention everywhere weight and macros are represented (History table, Log page, any future screens).

## Colors (global level)

Define in `src/app/globals.css` as CSS variables so light and dark mode can share or override:

| Nutrient | Text color | Accent (slightly darker) | CSS variable |
|----------|------------|---------------------------|--------------|
| Protein  | `#E9967A`  | Slightly darker variant   | `--macro-protein` / `--macro-protein-accent` |
| Carbs    | `#849B84`  | Slightly darker variant   | `--macro-carbs` / `--macro-carbs-accent` |
| Fats     | `#A9A444`  | Slightly darker variant   | `--macro-fat` / `--macro-fat-accent` |

- **Text color:** Use the variable for label and value text (e.g. `color: var(--macro-protein)`).
- **Accent:** Use the accent variable for hover/editable backgrounds and other “highlight” gestures (e.g. `background-color: var(--macro-protein-accent)`).
- In **dark mode** (`.dark`), reuse or tune these values for contrast (e.g. adjust carbs if needed on dark background).

## Icons (Lucide)

Use these **exact** icons from `lucide-react` for consistent representation:

| Concept  | Lucide icon   | Import name  |
|----------|----------------|--------------|
| Weight   | scale          | `Scale`      |
| Protein  | beef           | `Beef`       |
| Carbs    | croissant      | `Croissant`  |
| Fats     | droplet        | `Droplet`    |
| Calories | flame          | `Flame`      |

- Render the icon next to the label (e.g. first column of each row in History, or beside inputs on the Log page).
- **Weight** and **Calories:** icon uses default foreground color; no special text colors.
- **Protein / Carbs / Fats:** icon color matches the row’s macro color (e.g. `var(--macro-protein)`).
- Size: align with surrounding text; in History macro rows use **75%** font size, so icon size ~75% (e.g. `size-3.5`).


Keep this convention consistent across the app so the same colors and icons always represent the same concepts.
